For each speaker pair $\{i,j\}\in\binom{[K]}{2}$, select a set of frames $P_{i,j}$ not containing speakers other than $i$ and $j$:
\begin{equation}
P_{i,j}=[T]\setminus\bigcup_{k\in[K]\setminus\{i,j\}}T_k.
\end{equation}
We then process speaker pairs in descending order of $|P_{i,j}|$ to minimize the impact of diarization errors (impurities) in the selected frames.
